{"title_page": "2020 United Nations Climate Change Conference", "text_new": "{{Use Oxford English|date = February 2020}}\n{{Use dmy dates|date=February 2020}}\n{{Infobox event\n| title                    = 2020 United Nations Climate Change Conference\n| image                    = \n| image_upright            = \n| image_alt                = \n| caption                  = \n| native_name              = \n| native_name_lang         = \n| english_name             = \n| time                     = \n| duration                 = \n| date                     = ''Postponed to 2021'' \n| venue                    = [[SEC Centre]]\n| location                 = [[Glasgow]], [[Scotland]]\n| coordinates              = \n| also_known_as            = \n| type                     = \n| theme                    = \n| cause                    = \n| motive                   = \n| target                   = \n| first_reporter           = \n| budget                   = \n| organizers               = UK and Italy\n| filmed_by                = \n| participants             = [[United Nations Framework Convention on Climate Change|UNFCCC]] member countries\n| outcome                  = \n| casualties1              = \n| casualties2              = \n| casualties3              = \n| reported deaths          = \n| reported injuries        = \n| reported missing         = \n| reported property damage = \n| burial                   = \n| inquiries                = \n| inquest                  = \n| coroner                  = \n| arrests                  = \n| suspects                 = \n| accused                  = \n| convicted                = \n| charges                  = \n| trial                    = \n| verdict                  = \n| convictions              = \n| sentence                 = \n| publication_bans         = \n| litigation               = \n| awards                   = \n| blank1_label             = President\n| blank1_data              = [[Alok Sharma]]\n| blank2_label             = Previous event\n| blank2_data              = [[2019 United Nations Climate Change Conference|Madrid 2019]]\n| website                  ={{Official URL}} \n| notes                    = \n}}\n\nThe '''2020 United Nations Climate Change Conference''', also known as '''COP26''', is the 26th [[United Nations Climate Change conference]]. It was scheduled to be held in [[Glasgow]], [[Scotland]] from 9 to 20 November 2020 under the presidency of the [[Government of the United Kingdom|UK Government]] (with assistance from the [[Scottish Government]]).<ref name=eciu/> The conference is set to incorporate the 26th [[Conference of the parties|Conference of the Parties]] to the [[United Nations Framework Convention on Climate Change]] (UNFCCC), the 16th meeting of the parties to the [[Kyoto Protocol]] ('''CMP16'''), and the third meeting of the parties to the [[Paris Agreement]] ('''CMA3''').\n\nThis conference was set to have been the first \"global stocktake\" that was outlined in the [[Paris Agreement]].<ref name=\":0\">{{Cite web|url=https://blog.alfaenergygroup.com/the-importance-of-cop26/|title=The Importance of COP26|last=MSc|first=Nick Fedson MEng|date=2019-08-21|website=The Energy Compass|language=en-US|access-date=2020-04-02}}</ref>\n\nThe conference was scheduled to be held at the [[SEC Centre]] in Central Glasgow. On April 1, 2020 it was announced that the conference had been postponed, to an undetermined date in 2021, in light of the [[COVID-19 pandemic]]. The SEC Centre is being converted to an emergency hospital.<ref name=\":1\">{{Cite web|url=https://www.washingtonpost.com/climate-environment/2020/04/01/un-climate-coronavirus-cop26/|title=Amid pandemic, U.N. cancels global climate conference|last=Dennis|first=Brady|last2=Mooney|first2=Chris|date=|website=Washington Post|language=en|url-status=live|archive-url=|archive-date=|access-date=2020-04-01|last3=change|first3=|last4=energy|last5=|first5=}}</ref>\n\n==Presidency==\nFormer UK Minister for Energy and Clean Growth, [[Claire Perry O'Neill]], was originally appointed President of COP26,<ref name=unfccc /> but the UK government abruptly removed her on 31 January 2020, stating that the post would become \"a ministerial role\".<ref>{{cite news|work=[[BBC News Online]]|title=Climate change: UK sacks its UN conference president|first=David|last=Shukman|date=31 January 2020|accessdate=2020-01-31|url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/news/science-environment-51334031}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://inews.co.uk/news/politics/climate-change-summit-chief-claire-perry-o-neill-sacked-1382226|title=Climate change summit chief sacked by PM ahead of Cabinet reshuffle|website=inews.co.uk|language=en|access-date=2020-02-01}}</ref> Former Prime Minister [[David Cameron]] and former Foreign Secretary [[William Hague]] were unwilling to accept the position.<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.theguardian.com/environment/2020/feb/07/mary-robinson-attacks-unhelpful-uk-over-cop-26-climate-talks |title=UK unprepared for COP 26 conference, warn climate leaders |last=Harvey|first=Fiona|newspaper=The Guardian|date= 7 February 2020}}</ref> On 13 February, [[Conservative Party (UK)|Conservative]] minister [[Alok Sharma]] was appointed to the role.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.theguardian.com/politics/2020/feb/13/alok-sharma-appointed-chair-of-cop26-climate-conference-in-reshuffle|title=Alok Sharma appointed chair of COP26 climate conference in reshuffle|last=Harvey|first=Fiona|date=13 February 2020|website=The Guardian|url-status=live|archive-url=|archive-date=|access-date=2020-02-13}}</ref> Nigel Topping was appointed as the UK government's High Level Climate Action Champion for COP26;<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.ukcop26.org/nigel-topping-appointed-uk-high-level-climate-action-champion/|title=Nigel Topping appointed UK High Level Climate Action Champion|last=|first=|date=2020-01-23|website=UN Climate Change Conference (COP26)|language=en-GB|url-status=live|archive-url=|archive-date=|access-date=2020-04-09}}</ref> he is the former CEO of We Mean Business, a climate change action organisation.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.wemeanbusinesscoalition.org/blog/nigel-topping-2/|title=Getting ready for the decade of delivery|date=2019-12-18|website=We Mean Business Coalition|language=en|access-date=2020-04-09}}</ref> Also appointed by the Prime Minister and taking a finance advisory position is [[Mark Carney]], former governor of the [[Bank of England]].<ref>https://www.ukcop26.org/mark-carney-to-drive-finance-action-for-uk-climate-talks/</ref>\n\nPartnering the UK in leading COP26 will be Italy. For the most part, their role will be in preparatory work such as the hosting of a pre-COP session and an event for young people called Youth4Climate 2020: Driving Ambition. These events were scheduled to take place between 28 September and 2 October in [[Milan]].<ref>https://www.minambiente.it/pagina/cop-26-pre-cop-and-youth-event-youth4climate-2020-driving-ambition</ref>\n\n== Global Stocktake ==\nUnder the [[Paris Agreement]], countries submitted [[Intended nationally determined contributions]], to reduce [[Greenhouse gas|greenhouse gas emissions]] compared to a \"business as usual\" scenario. Under the framework of the Paris Agreement, each country was expected to submit enhanced nationally determined contributions every five years, to ratchet up ambition to mitigate climate change.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://unfccc.int/process-and-meetings/the-paris-agreement/the-paris-agreement|title=The Paris Agreement|last=|first=|date=|website=unfccc.int|url-status=live|archive-url=|archive-date=|access-date=2020-04-02}}</ref> Since the Paris Agreement was signed in 2015, at the [[2015 United Nations Climate Change Conference]], the conference of 2020 was set to be the first global stocktake.<ref name=\":0\" />\n\n==Postponement==\nIn light of the unprecedented [[COVID-19 pandemic]], the Conference of Parties was postponed to an unspecified date in 2021.<ref>{{Cite news|last=Jillian|first=Ambrose|url=https://www.theguardian.com/environment/2020/apr/01/uk-likely-to-postpone-cop26-un-climate-talks-glasgow-coronavirus|title=Cop26 climate talks in Glasgow postponed until 2021|date=2020-04-01|work=The Guardian|access-date=2020-04-02|url-status=live|language=en-GB|issn=0261-3077}}</ref> The host nations [[COVID-19 pandemic in Italy|Italy]] and the [[COVID-19 pandemic in the United Kingdom|United Kingdom]] were very heavily affected by the pandemic, and the venue of the conference, the SEC Centre in Glasgow, had been converted into a field hospital for COVID patients.<ref name=\":1\" />\n\nUNFCCC Secretary [[Patricia Espinosa]] tweeted that \"in light of the ongoing, worldwide effects of COVID-19, holding an ambitious, inclusive, COP26 in November 2020 is not possible.\"<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://twitter.com/PEspinosaC/status/1245452695219159040|title=The Bureau decided to also postpone #COP26 , in a date to be set after the #COP26 presidency consults with all Parties. The Bureau assessed that in light of the ongoing, worldwide effects of #COVID\u30fc19, holding an ambitious, inclusive COP26 in November 2020 is no possible.|last=C|first=Patricia Espinosa|date=2020-04-01|website=@PEspinosaC|language=en|access-date=2020-04-02}}</ref> She also indicated that when economies restart, this will be an opportunity to \"shape the 21st century economy in ways that are clean, green, healthy, just, safe and more resilient.\"<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://twitter.com/PEspinosaC/status/1245452695219159040|title=The Bureau decided to also postpone #COP26 , in a date to be set after the #COP26 presidency consults with all Parties. The Bureau assessed that in light of the ongoing, worldwide effects of #COVID\u30fc19, holding an ambitious, inclusive COP26 in November 2020 is no possible.|last=C|first=Patricia Espinosa|date=2020-04-01|website=@PEspinosaC|language=en|access-date=2020-04-02}}</ref>\n\nIndependent observers noted that though not directly related, the postponement will give the international community time to respond to the outcome of the [[2020 United States presidential election|United States presidential election]]. This is crucial because incumbent president [[Donald Trump]] has pledged to withdraw the United States from the [[Paris Agreement]], but can only do this if he wins this election; while his [[Democratic Party (United States)|Democratic]] challengers have pledged to stay in the Paris Agreement and increase ambition to reduce emissions.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://insideclimatenews.org/news/01042020/cop-26-glasgow-delay-coronavirus-covid-united-nations|title=COP\u2019s Postponement Until 2021 Gives World Leaders Time to Respond to U.S. Election|last=Gustin|first=Georgina|date=2020-04-01|website=InsideClimate News|language=en-US|access-date=2020-04-02}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.climatechangenews.com/2020/04/01/cop26-climate-talks-postponed-2021-amid-coronavirus-pandemic/|title=Cop26 climate talks postponed to 2021 amid coronavirus pandemic|date=2020-04-01|website=Climate Home News|language=en|access-date=2020-04-02}}</ref>\n\n==References==\n{{Portal|Environment|Climate change|Scotland}}\n{{reflist|refs=\n<ref name=eciu>\n{{cite web\n| url=https://eciu.net/briefings/international-perspectives/cop-26\n| title=UK to host 2020 UN climate summit, COP26\n| author=<!--Not stated-->\n| date=\n| website=\n| publisher=The Energy and Climate Intelligence Unit\n| access-date=2019-12-16\n| quote=\n}}\n</ref>\n<ref name=unfccc>\n{{Cite web\n|url=https://unfccc.int/news/united-kingdom-in-partnership-with-italy-to-host-cop-26/cmp-16/cma-3\n|title=United Kingdom, in partnership with Italy, to host COP 26 / CMP 16 / CMA 3\n|publisher= [[UNFCCC]]\n|date=2019-09-25\n|access-date=2019-11-29\n}}\n</ref>\n}}\n\n== External links ==\n{{Official website}}\n\n{{United Nations climate change conferences}}\n\n[[Category:2021 conferences]]\n[[Category:2021 in Scotland]]\n[[Category:2021 in the environment]]\n[[Category:United Nations climate change conferences]]\n[[Category:Events in Glasgow]]\n[[Category:Events postponed due to the 2019\u201320 coronavirus pandemic|United Nations Climate Change Conference, 2020]]\n[[Category:21st century in Glasgow]]\n", "text_old": "{{Use Oxford English|date = February 2020}}\n{{Use dmy dates|date=February 2020}}\n{{Infobox event\n| title                    = 2020 United Nations Climate Change Conference\n| image                    = \n| image_upright            = \n| image_alt                = \n| caption                  = \n| native_name              = \n| native_name_lang         = \n| english_name             = \n| time                     = \n| duration                 = \n| date                     = ''Postponed to 2021'' \n| venue                    = [[SEC Centre]]\n| location                 = [[Glasgow]], [[Scotland]]\n| coordinates              = \n| also_known_as            = \n| type                     = \n| theme                    = \n| cause                    = \n| motive                   = \n| target                   = \n| first_reporter           = \n| budget                   = \n| organizers               = UK and Italy\n| filmed_by                = \n| participants             = [[United Nations Framework Convention on Climate Change|UNFCCC]] member countries\n| outcome                  = \n| casualties1              = \n| casualties2              = \n| casualties3              = \n| reported deaths          = \n| reported injuries        = \n| reported missing         = \n| reported property damage = \n| burial                   = \n| inquiries                = \n| inquest                  = \n| coroner                  = \n| arrests                  = \n| suspects                 = \n| accused                  = \n| convicted                = \n| charges                  = \n| trial                    = \n| verdict                  = \n| convictions              = \n| sentence                 = \n| publication_bans       