l Climate Action Champion|last=|first=|date=2020-01-23|website=UN Climate Change Conference (COP26)|language=en-GB|url-status=live|archive-url=|archive-date=|access-date=2020-04-09}}</ref> he is the former CEO of We Mean Business, a climate change action organisation.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.wemeanbusinesscoalition.org/blog/nigel-topping-2/|title=Getting ready for the decade of delivery|date=2019-12-18|website=We Mean Business Coalition|language=en|access-date=2020-04-09}}</ref> Also appointed by the Prime Minister and taking a finance advisory position is [[Mark Carney]], former governor of the [[Bank of England]].<ref>https://www.ukcop26.org/mark-carney-to-drive-finance-action-for-uk-climate-talks/</ref>\n\nPartnering the UK in leading COP26 will be Italy. For the most part, their role will be in preparatory work such as the hosting of a pre-COP session and an event for young people called Youth4Climate 2020: Driving Ambition. These events were scheduled to take place between 28 September and 2 October in [[Milan]].<ref>https://www.minambiente.it/pagina/cop-26-pre-cop-and-youth-event-youth4climate-2020-driving-ambition</ref>\n\n== Global Stocktake ==\nUnder the [[Paris Agreement]], countries submitted [[Intended nationally determined contributions]], to reduce [[Greenhouse gas|greenhouse gas emissions]] compared to a \"business as usual\" scenario. Under the framework of the Paris Agreement, each country was expected to submit enhanced nationally determined contributions every five years, to ratchet up ambition to mitigate climate change.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://unfccc.int/process-and-meetings/the-paris-agreement/the-paris-agreement|title=The Paris Agreement|last=|first=|date=|website=unfccc.int|url-status=live|archive-url=|archive-date=|access-date=2020-04-02}}</ref> Since the Paris Agreement was signed in 2015, at the [[2015 United Nations Climate Change Conference]], the conference of 2020 was set to be the first global stocktake.<ref name=\":0\" />\n\n==Postponement==\nIn light of the unprecedented [[2019\u201320 coronavirus pandemic]], the Conference of Parties was postponed to an unspecified date in 2021.<ref>{{Cite news|last=Jillian|first=Ambrose|url=https://www.theguardian.com/environment/2020/apr/01/uk-likely-to-postpone-cop26-un-climate-talks-glasgow-coronavirus|title=Cop26 climate talks in Glasgow postponed until 2021|date=2020-04-01|work=The Guardian|access-date=2020-04-02|url-status=live|language=en-GB|issn=0261-3077}}</ref> The host nations [[2020 coronavirus pandemic in Italy|Italy]] and the [[COVID-19 pandemic in the United Kingdom|United Kingdom]] were very heavily affected by the pandemic, and the venue of the conference, the SEC Centre in Glasgow, had been converted into a field hospital for COVID patients.<ref name=\":1\" />\n\nUNFCCC Secretary [[Patricia Espinosa]] tweeted that \"in light of the ongoing, worldwide effects of COVID-19, holding an ambitious, inclusive, COP26 in November 2020 is not possible.\"<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://twitter.com/PEspinosaC/status/1245452695219159040|title=The Bureau decided to also postpone #COP26 , in a date to be set after the #COP26 presidency consults with all Parties. The Bureau assessed that in light of the ongoing, worldwide effects of #COVID\u30fc19, holding an ambitious, inclusive COP26 in November 2020 is no possible.|last=C|first=Patricia Espinosa|date=2020-04-01|website=@PEspinosaC|language=en|access-date=2020-04-02}}</ref> She also indicated that when economies restart, this will be an opportunity to \"shape the 21st century economy in ways that are clean, green, healthy, just, safe and more resilient.\"<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://twitter.com/PEspinosaC/status/1245452695219159040|title=The Bureau decided to also postpone #COP26 , in a date to be set after the #COP26 presidency consults with all Parties. The Bureau assessed that in light of the ongoing, worldwide effects of #COVID\u30fc19, holding an ambitious, inclusive COP26 in November 2020 is no possible.|last=C|first=Patricia Espinosa|date=2020-04-01|website=@PEspinosaC|language=en|access-date=2020-04-02}}</ref>\n\nIndependent observers noted that though not directly related, the postponement will give the international community time to respond to the outcome of the [[2020 United States presidential election|United States presidential election]]. This is crucial because incumbent president [[Donald Trump]] has pledged to withdraw the United States from the [[Paris Agreement]], but can only do this if he wins this election; while his [[Democratic Party (United States)|Democratic]] challengers have pledged to stay in the Paris Agreement and increase ambition to reduce emissions.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://insideclimatenews.org/news/01042020/cop-26-glasgow-delay-coronavirus-covid-united-nations|title=COP\u2019s Postponement Until 2021 Gives World Leaders Time to Respond to U.S. Election|last=Gustin|first=Georgina|date=2020-04-01|website=InsideClimate News|language=en-US|access-date=2020-04-02}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.climatechangenews.com/2020/04/01/cop26-climate-talks-postponed-2021-amid-coronavirus-pandemic/|title=Cop26 climate talks postponed to 2021 amid coronavirus pandemic|date=2020-04-01|website=Climate Home News|language=en|access-date=2020-04-02}}</ref>\n\n==References==\n{{Portal|Environment|Climate change|Scotland}}\n{{reflist|refs=\n<ref name=eciu>\n{{cite web\n| url=https://eciu.net/briefings/international-perspectives/cop-26\n| title=UK to host 2020 UN climate summit, COP26\n| author=<!--Not stated-->\n| date=\n| website=\n| publisher=The Energy and Climate Intelligence Unit\n| access-date=2019-12-16\n| quote=\n}}\n</ref>\n<ref name=unfccc>\n{{Cite web\n|url=https://unfccc.int/news/united-kingdom-in-partnership-with-italy-to-host-cop-26/cmp-16/cma-3\n|title=United Kingdom, in partnership with Italy, to host COP 26 / CMP 16 / CMA 3\n|publisher= [[UNFCCC]]\n|date=2019-09-25\n|access-date=2019-11-29\n}}\n</ref>\n}}\n\n== External l